---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navigation from '../../components/Navigation.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Ultimate Guide to Lash Extension Aftercare | Elegant Lashes Orange County"
  description="Learn professional aftercare tips to make your lash extensions last longer and look beautiful. Essential advice from Orange County's top lash artists."
  keywords="lash extension aftercare, eyelash extension care, lash maintenance, Orange County lash care"
>
  <Navigation />

  <main class="pt-20 bg-lightbg">
    <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
      <!-- Back to Blog Link -->
      <a href="/blog" class="inline-flex items-center text-primary hover:text-primary/80 transition-colors mb-8">
        <svg class="w-5 h-5 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 19l-7-7m0 0l7-7m-7 7h18"></path>
        </svg>
        Back to Blog
      </a>

      <!-- Article Header -->
      <header class="mb-12">
        <div class="text-sm text-primary font-medium mb-4">July 15, 2025</div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold font-playfair text-darktext mb-6">Ultimate Guide to Lash Extension Aftercare</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-mediumtext">Learn professional aftercare tips to make your lash extensions last longer and look beautiful. Essential advice from Orange County's top lash artists.</p>
      </header>

      <!-- Article Content -->
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>Getting lash extensions is an investment in your beauty routine, and proper aftercare is essential to maximize their lifespan and keep them looking gorgeous. As Orange County's premier lash salon, we've compiled the ultimate aftercare guide based on our years of experience and thousands of satisfied clients.</p>

        <h2>The First 24-48 Hours: Critical Care Period</h2>
        <p>The first 24-48 hours after your lash extension application are crucial for proper bonding. During this time:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Avoid water, steam, and excessive humidity</li>
          <li>Skip your workout routine to prevent sweating</li>
          <li>Avoid oil-based products near your eyes</li>
          <li>Don't rub, pull, or play with your lashes</li>
          <li>Sleep on your back if possible</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Daily Lash Extension Care Routine</h2>
        <p>Once the initial bonding period is over, establish a daily care routine:</p>

        <h3>Morning Care:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Gently brush your lashes with a clean spoolie brush</li>
          <li>Use a gentle, oil-free cleanser around the eye area</li>
          <li>Pat dry with a clean towel</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Evening Care:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Remove all eye makeup with oil-free makeup remover</li>
          <li>Cleanse lashes with a lash extension-safe foam cleanser</li>
          <li>Rinse with lukewarm water</li>
          <li>Gently pat dry and brush through with a spoolie</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>What to Avoid with Lash Extensions</h2>
        <p>To keep your Orange County lash extensions looking their best, avoid:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Oil-based cleansers, makeup removers, and moisturizers</li>
          <li>Waterproof mascara (if you must use mascara, use water-based)</li>
          <li>Mechanical eyelash curlers</li>
          <li>Sleeping face-down on your pillow</li>
          <li>Picking, pulling, or rubbing your lashes</li>
          <li>Excessive heat from hair dryers or saunas</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Orange County Lifestyle Considerations</h2>
        <p>Living in Orange County means beach days, outdoor activities, and year-round sunshine. Here's how to protect your lashes:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Beach Days:</strong> Rinse lashes with fresh water after swimming in the ocean</li>
          <li><strong>Pool Time:</strong> Use protective eyewear when possible, rinse afterward</li>
          <li><strong>Hiking/Outdoor Activities:</strong> Wear sunglasses to protect from wind and debris</li>
          <li><strong>Sunny Weather:</strong> The extra vitamin D is great, but wear a hat for lash protection</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Fill Appointments: Maintaining Your Look</h2>
        <p>Regular fill appointments every 2-3 weeks are essential for maintaining your lash extensions. At our Orange County locations, we recommend:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Booking your next appointment before leaving the salon</li>
          <li>Coming in when you have 50-60% of your extensions remaining</li>
          <li>Avoiding the temptation to wait too long between fills</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>When to Contact Your Lash Artist</h2>
        <p>Reach out to your Orange County lash artist if you experience:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Unusual irritation or redness</li>
          <li>Significant lash loss within the first week</li>
          <li>Any concerns about the health of your natural lashes</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Following these aftercare guidelines will help ensure your lash extensions look beautiful and last as long as possible. At Elegant Lashes by Katie, we're always here to support you in maintaining your gorgeous Orange County lashes!</p>
      </div>

      <!-- CTA Section -->
      <div class="mt-16 bg-gradient-sunset p-8 rounded-xl text-center">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold font-playfair text-darktext mb-4">Ready for Beautiful Lashes?</h3>
        <p class="text-darktext mb-6">Visit us at one of our four convenient Orange County locations: Irvine, Tustin, Santa Ana, or Costa Mesa!</p>
        <button type="button" class="open-modal-button main-book-now-btn text-xl">
          <span>Book Now</span>
        </button>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

